ass="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/08/15/wp-yall/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1596:"<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/WordCamp-Birmingham-WP-Y-all.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-8386 size-full" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/WordCamp-Birmingham-WP-Y-all.png" alt="WordCamp Birmingham   WP Y all" width="639" height="150" /></a></p>\n<p>This year for <a href="http://2014.birmingham.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp Birmingham</a> aka WP Y&#8217;all, it is being held on Saturday, August 16th at the Harbert Center. During the WordCamp, you will have a chance to see WDS team member, <a title="Greg Rickaby" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/greg-rickaby/">Greg Rickaby</a>!</p>\n<p>This is only the second time that Greg will be presenting at a WordCamp, and it&#8217;s not a presentation you want to miss out on. He will be presenting about<span style="text-decoration: underline"> SASS Basics</span>. He is extremely passionate about SASS and believes in it wholeheartedly. Here is a short description of his presentation &#8211;</p>\n<blockquote><p>A high level, introduction to WordPress theming with Sass. Greg will cover basics such as Variables/Mixins/Nesting/Inheritance/Compilers and file structure.</p></blockquote>\n<p>You can see Greg on<strong> Saturday; August 16th at 9:50 AM</strong> in the Design/Business Track.</p>\n<p>If you miss out on his presentation, you will be able talk to him at the after party on Saturday. Don&#8217;t be afraid to walk up to him and ask him questions about SASS or WordPress in general. He is excited to expand his knowledge and to meet people who share his love for WordPress!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:49:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/08/15/wp-yall/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:57:"\n   \n    \n    \n    \n    \n        \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n\n    \n    \n        \n      \n    \n    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"Dre Armeda Joins WebDevStudios";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/08/14/dre-armeda-joins-webdevstudios/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/08/14/dre-armeda-joins-webdevstudios/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 14 Aug 2014 15:00:45 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Employee Post";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"dre armeda";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"executive team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"leadership";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"operations";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8404";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:422:"In May 2014, Dre Armeda announced that he was stepping down as CEO of Sucuri, Inc., a business that he started 4 years ago and turned into a very successful multi-million dollar, 30+ employee company that services millions of unique monthly scans, monitors &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/08/14/dre-armeda-joins-webdevstudios/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Lisa Sabin-Wilson";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3882:"<p><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-8405" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/dre-armeda-300x300.jpg" alt="Dre Armeda Joins WebDevStudios" width="300" height="300" />In May 2014, Dre Armeda <a href="http://dremeda.com/fair-winds-and-following-seas-sucuri/">announced</a> that he was stepping down as CEO of Sucuri, Inc., a business that he started 4 years ago and turned into a very successful multi-million dollar, 30+ employee company that services millions of unique monthly scans, monitors thousands of websites, and makes sure that 100′s of websites are cleared of malware daily.  As a CISSP, Dre is a recognized expert in the field of Information Security.</p>\n<p>We are very proud, and excited, to announce that Dre has joined our leadership team here at WebDevStudios and has stepped into the role of VP of Operations with a focus on organizational and business development, talent development and strategy.</p>\n<p>Prior to running Sucuri, Dre was the founder of <em>Cubic 2</em>, a custom web design &amp; development shop that provided custom solutions for WordPress clients.  If that sounds familiar, that&#8217;s because that&#8217;s what we do here at WebDevStudios.  We are excited about bringing Dre&#8217;s experience and expertise into our team here at WDS, as we know his years of experience in information security &amp; architecture, managing remote teams, and his achievements in building and scaling a successful business will bring great value to our clients, and team, here at WebDevStudios.</p>\n<p>Dre&#8217;s excitement for open source software matches our own, and his passion for the WordPress project, in particular, is evident in his contributions to the community.  As a popular, and regular, <a href="http://wordpress.tv/speakers/dre-armeda/">speaker at WordCamps</a>, and related events, he is responsible for making an entire community of users and developers more aware of the importance of securing code and web sites by presenting it in a way that is easy to understand, while at the same time instilling a sense of urgency around making sure we all are doing what we can to secure our data and sites from the various risks out there in the WWW.</p>\n<p><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-8406" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/dradcast.png" alt="DradCast" width="200" height="223" />Dre also contributes to this community by way of a very popular, and informational, podcast that he co-hosts with our own Brad Williams.  <a href="http://dradcast.com">DradCast</a> airs every Wednesday evening at 8pm ET and is a show that primarily concentrates on the latest news around WordPress, upcoming WordPress events, and the wonderful community surrounding the premiere open source content management system on the internet.</p>\n<p>On a personal level, Dre resides in southern California and is a Harley enthusiast, a Chargers fan and he loves tacos. Having spent several years in the Navy, he shares the esteemed title of &#8220;former military geek&#8221; with Brad and Brian (both former Marines).</p>\n<p>We are thrilled to have Dre join our executive team here at WebDevStudios.  As we continue to grow and mature as a company, he plays a significant role in helping lead us into the future.  Our executive team is now complete with <a title="Brad Williams" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-williams/">Brad Williams</a>(CEO), <a title="Lisa Sabin-Wilson" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/lisa-sabin-wilson/">Lisa Sabin-Wilson</a> (COO), <a title="Brian Messenlehner" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-messenlehner/">Brian Messenlehner</a> (CTO) and now the addition of Dre Armeda as VP of Operations, we are excited for the future of our team and for our clients!</p>\n<p>Please join us in welcoming Dre as the newest member to the WDS team!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/08/14/dre-armeda-joins-webdevstudios/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"6";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b: