(66, 1, '2014-06-24 22:30:03', '2014-06-24 22:30:03', '<a name="WhatWeDo"><strong>What we Do</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://gbd.fwd.wf/sfnct/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/about_us.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-103" src="https://gbd.fwd.wf/sfnct/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/about_us.jpg" alt="about_us" width="300" height="203" /></a>\r\n\r\nSFNCT came together in 2001 through the initiative and support of the San Francisco Mayor''s Office of Community Development (MOCD), which is now the Mayor''s Office of Housing, Community Development Division.\r\n\r\nFormer MOCD Director Pamela David recognized the value and importance of the Neighborhood Centers. She also recognized the challenges faced by these anchor institutions in the form of categorical funding that did not support their essential community building and community organizing work. Ms. David convened a meeting for Executive Directors of Neighborhood Centers to discuss ways for MOCD to support their leaders and their work.\r\n\r\nThe group continued to meet, building strong connections between the Neighborhood Centers, and between these agencies and MOCD. In late 2001 Executive Directors of the participating agencies, with the support of MOCD, launched San Francisco Neighborhood Centers Together to:\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>Advocate for the Neighborhood Center/Settlement House model as an effective solution for addressing social and economic issues</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Build and strengthen connections between Neighborhood Centers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>Increase dialogue between the Neighborhood Centers and City officials</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>Design and implement collaborative projects</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>Share information, resources, and "back-office" services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Provide peer mentoring and support for Neighborhood Center leaders</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Facilitate successful leadership transitions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Communicate the value, impact, and accomplishments of the Neighborhood Centers to funders, stakeholders, and City officials</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name="History"><strong>History</strong></a>\r\n\r\nSFNCT members have been collaborating, sharing services, and building agency, individual, and community capacity since our founding as a network in 2001.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'About Us', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about_us', '', '', '2014-07-11 14:04:48', '2014-07-11 14:04:48', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/sfnct/?page_id=66', 0, 'page', '', 0),
